    &lt;Title&gt;Head Injury ~ Discharged without examination!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I fell in my Wet Room - Cracking my head against wall and jarring my lower back. I was unable to stand, so crawled to lounge and called 999. Ambulance crew arrived promptly examined the wound and recommended I went to Russell Hall Hospital for examination, as I am on Warfarin  and very unsteady on my feet. Nursing staff wanted to know exactly what had happened. I had bloods taken, Blood Pressure &amp;amp; ECG. A Doctor asked me the same questions, "what exactly happened". I explained that for a couple of weeks I had felt dizzy and my local surgery checked my ears - The Hospital Doctor then sent me to have a CT Scan. Four hours since falling down and still bleeding on both CT Scan Head Brace &amp;amp; on A&amp;amp;E Cubical Stretcher - At NO time was my wound examined or cleaned by any of the Health Professionals - A Doctor came to see me with the good news that there was no bleeds on the brain or irregular scan / blood test results. I was told I was free to leave and discharged. I explained that I am disabled with mobility issues and lived alone. I still have a thumping headache and feeling of disorientation - six hours since my fall. I asked if there was any Patients Transport available, but told that is reserved for only Disabled, Elderly or those with Mental Health issues. So it appears that a patient who has Dilated Cardiomyopathy, suffering from imbalance issues, bleeding following a head wound, in severe pain lower back and hip is NOT considered disabled ?????????? I then requested a Taxi suitable for my health needs. Thankfully I had a Taxi Driver who was able to help me in / out of vehicle and safely into my home. So NO I do not recommend Russell Hall Hospital. CLEAN /  EXAMINE Wound is Basic FIRST AID!!!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
